author: nininhosam
text:
​ @JV  You mean like this?
it's pretty simple. it's just a space bar. but since youtube doesn't let you post "just a space" there's also an invisible character. the character in question is the character that makes text inverted (left to right, it's used when you mix two different languages such as arabic which writes from right to left, with ours which is the opposite, for example). there are a couple of invisible characters which are essentially "functions" and this is one of them. 
Also, this explanation is from my memory of a couple-of-years-old video so if you want accuracy, you should probably search more about it yourself, but that's the gist of it
